{{Navlist/Top}}

This section covers advanced topics in phonetics (sounds) and phonology (systems of sounds).

== What's in this section? ==

The parts of this section are:
*'''Common sounds''':  Technical details that weren't covered in the Intermediate section, about sounds that ''were'' covered &mdash; things like gemination, diphthongs, and suprasegmentals.
*'''Unusual sounds''':  Sounds that humans can produce, but that don't often occur in the world's languages, like clicks and pharyngeals.
*'''Non-human phonologies''':  What kinds of phonetics and phonology might apply to a language whose speakers aren't human.<br/>&nbsp;

{{Navlist/Bottom}}

