{{Chess Opening Theory/Position|= |Ruy Lopez Open Defence| |rd| | |qd|kd|bd| |rd|= | | |pd| | |pd|pd|pd|= |pd| |nd| |bd| | | |= | |pd| |pd|pl| | | |= | | | | |nd| | | |= | |bl|pl| | |nl| | |= |pl|pl| | | |pl|pl|pl|= |rl|nl|bl|ql| |rl|kl| |= |parent=[[Chess/Ruy Lopez|Ruy Lopez]] }}
=Ruy Lopez Open Defence=
At this point there are two main lines, which are Bc5 and Be7.
{{BookCat}}

{{Chess Opening Theory/Position|= |Ruy Lopez Open Defence| |rd| | |qd|kd|bd| |rd|= | | |pd| | |pd|pd|pd|= |pd| |nd| |bd| | | |= | |pd| |pd|pl| | | |= | | | | |nd| | | |= | |bl| | | |nl| | |= |pl|pl|pl|nl| |pl|pl|pl|= |rl| |bl|ql| |rl|kl| |= |parent=[[Chess/Ruy Lopez|Ruy Lopez]] }}
=Ruy Lopez Open Defence=
The old line goes: 9...Nc5 10. c3 d4 11. cxd4 Nxd4. The new variation goes: 11.Ng5!? Qxg5. Black is thought to equalize in both lines.
{{BookCat}}

